From f58c2bae1b9e851ab069d68905b4e69ae83603c1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 18:09:30 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 9.5 Session A: KrtPrCommentController surfaces existing
 review comments natively
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Foundation for the comments-API migration laid out in
docs/phases/phase-09-5-native-comments.md. Adds:

- krtPrCommentRegistry.ts: per-URI metadata (side, path, realLines,
  PR identity) populated by KrtMonacoDiffView on construct.
- krtPrCommentThread.ts: minimal CommentThread<IRange> impl.
- krtPrCommentController.ts: ICommentController + IKrtPrCommentController
  decorator. Maps the per-URI registry through to native threads on
  setCommentsForPr; computes commentingRanges from realLines so the
  workbench's CommentController contribution renders the native '+'
  gutter affordance.
- KrtMonacoDiffView: registers base/head URIs on construct and
  allow-lists 'editor.contrib.review' on the inner editors so the
  workbench's CommentController attaches.
- KrtPullRequestEditorPane: pushes loaded review comments through the
  controller after loadReviewComments / on cache hit / on
  postReviewComment success; clears on PR switch.

Custom .krt-pr-diff-thread view zones still render below the native
threads — duplicate UI is the accepted intermediate. Session B
(native +-click → post via IPullRequestProvider) and Session C
(remove the custom overlay) come next.
